  "prompt": "What is the interview process at JusPay Bangalore?",
  "response": "Based on available information, here's a typical interview process at JusPay Bangalore:\n\n1. Initial Screening\n- Resume shortlisting\n- Initial phone/HR screening\n- Basic technical and background discussion\n\n2. Technical Rounds\n- Usually 2-3 technical interview rounds\n- Focus on:\n  - Data structures and algorithms\n  - System design\n  - Problem-solving skills\n  - Coding challenges\n  - Technical depth in relevant technologies\n\n3. Coding Assessment\n- Online coding test\n- Algorithmic problem-solving\n- Data structure questions\n- Platform might be HackerRank or similar\n\n4. System Design Round\n- Evaluating candidate's ability to design scalable systems\n- Discussion of architectural approaches\n- Understanding of distributed systems\n\n5. Manager/Leadership Interview\n- Cultural fit assessment\n- Discussion of past projects\n- Understanding of organizational fit\n\n6. Final HR/Managerial Discussion\n- Salary negotiation\n- Role-specific details\n- Final selection decision\n\nExact process may vary depending on specific role and team requirements. Candidates are typically evaluated on technical skills, problem-solving ability, and cultural alignment.\n\nNote: This is a general overview based on typical tech company interview processes and may not reflect the exact current process at JusPay.",
